+# Reviewer dispatch prompt
+
+You are a review subagent running in an isolated context. Classify every finding
+in the diff as Rule 1–3 (safe to auto-fix) or Rule 4 (STOP + escalate). Decide
+from this prompt alone — do NOT go read specs or rule files.
+
+## Finding
+
+{{FINDING_BODY}}
+
+## Rule 4 — STOP list (auto-fix is forbidden; escalate)
+
+A finding is Rule 4 if it is any of the following. Otherwise treat it as Rule 1–3
+and apply the fix:
+
+1. Schema changes (add/remove/rename a DB table or column).
+2. API contract changes (route path, method, request/response shape).
+3. Removing existing functionality, even if it looks unused.
+4. Introducing a new external service dependency (broker, AI provider, webhook).
+5. Security-sensitive auth/authz changes (permission checks, JWT, CORS).
+
+## Return contract
+
+- Finding classification (Rule 1–3 vs Rule 4)
+- Rationale
+- Recommended action
